{"title":"•Amoxicilina-clavulanato-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/•Amoxicilina-clavulanato-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"• Amoxicilina-clavulanato","guid":"XijmsJbR_e8kJbT5HkxDjw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Uso y\\NDosificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Estructura:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Amoxicilina-clavulanato es una aminopenicilina + inhibidor de β-lactamasa.\\NClavulanato extiende el espectro a bacterias productoras de β-lactamasa seleccionadas.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Formulaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"• Tableta de liberación inmediata, tableta de liberación\\Nprolongada (ER), tableta masticable, suspensión oral.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"• Formulación IV disponible en algunos lugares (no en EE.UU.)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"• Dosis: Basadas en el componente de Amoxicilina, expresadas en mg\\Ncomo componente de Amoxicilina/Clavulanato, e.g., 500 mg/125 mg.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"• Riesgo en embarazo\\Ny lactancia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"• Categoría de riesgo FDA 1: Sin evidencia de toxicidad en humanos o animales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"• Uso durante lactancia: Concentraciones bajas en leche, no se esperan efectos adversos. Monitorear toxicidad GI en el infante.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en\\NAdultos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Amox-Clav (500 mg/125 mg) 1 tab po q8h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Amox-Clav (875 mg/125 mg) 1 tab po q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"• Amox-Clav ER (1000 mg/62. 5 mg) 2 tabs po q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"11","text":"• Amox-Clav (1000 mg/200 mg) IV q8h (donde disponible)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en\\NPediatría","guid":"","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Dosis (Edad >28 días)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"• 45 mg/kg/día (dividido q12h) [formulación 7:1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"16","text":"• 90 mg/kg/día (dividido q12h) para <40 kg [formulación 14:1, para AOM]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"16","text":"• IV (formulación 5:1):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• <3 meses o <4 kg: 25 mg/5 mg por kg q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• ≥3 meses: 25 mg/5 mg por kg q8h","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Renal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Peso corporal y depuración de creatinina (CrCl):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Clavulanato es eliminado por el hígado, no por el riñón.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"• Función Renal\\NNormal vs. ESRD:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"• Vida media (hr): Amox 1.4, Clav 1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"• Vida media (ESRD): Amox 5-20, Clav 4","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"23","text":"• Dosis (PO):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"• CrCl >30: Sin ajuste de dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"• CrCl 10-30: 250-500 mg (amox) q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"• CrCl <10: 250-500 mg (amox) q24h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"29","text":"• HD: 250-500 mg (amox) q24h (+ dosis extra AD)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Hepático: Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"1","text":"Efectos\\NAdversos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"• Mononucleosis infecciosa (EBV): ↑ Rash. No es alergia permanente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"• Alergia a Amoxicilina: ↑ Riesgo de reacciones cruzadas con cefalosporinas orales con cadena lateral R1 idéntica: Cefadroxil, Cefprozil.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"35","text":"• Hepatotoxicidad: Asociada con ácido clavulánico. Amoxicilina-clavulanato es la causa más común (13-23%)\\Nde lesión hepática colestásica inducida por medicamentos. Predisposición genética.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"35","text":"• Otros efectos: Fiebre, rash (3%), anafilaxia (raro), neutropenia, eosinofilia, trombocitopenia (raro),\\Nnáuseas/vómitos (3%), diarrea (9%), colitis por C. difficile, ↑ LFTs, cefalea, convulsiones (raro).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"35","text":"• Regímenes bid: Menos clavulanato y menos diarrea.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"35","text":"• Reacción alérgica inmediata: 1/3 se deben al clavulanato.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"35","text":"• **Prueba de sangre positiva para 1,3 beta D-glucano en pacientes con amoxicilina-clavulanato IV.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"0","text":"Espectro\\NAntimicrobiano","guid":"","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"RECOMENDADO ++ (6)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• B. fragilis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"• Capnocytophaga sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"• H. influenzae","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"44","text":"• M. catarrhalis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"44","text":"• P. multocida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"44","text":"• S. saprophyticus","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"43","text":"ACTIVO + (31)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"• Actinomyces sp.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","p